<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870121-0067 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:J.P. Morgan's Olds to HeadIts New Securities Group</HL><DD> 01/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS JPM </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   In anticipation of expanded securities activities, J.P. Morgan andamp; Co. said it consolidated its world-wide securities businesses into a new securities group.    It also named John T. Olds, who previously was in charge of Morgan's business operations in Asia and the Pacific, to head the new unit.    Mr. Olds, an executive vice president of Morgan Guaranty Trust Co., the bank holding company's principal banking unit, was also named executive vice president of the holding company. Morgan said Mr. Olds, 43 years old, will be responsible for developing the company's securities strategy and will report to its corporate office.    Included in the new unit will be J.P. Morgan Securities Inc., a subsidiary responsible for money-market trading, public finance, and underwriting and trading government and municipal securities; J.P. Morgan Equities Inc., which will house a full-service brokerage operation if an application currently pending before the Federal Reserve Board is approved; and other units involved in securities administration and operations.    William R. Barrett, 44, a senior vice president of Morgan Guaranty and manager of its Tokyo office, will succeed Mr. Olds as head of business operations in the Asia and Pacific region. </TEXT></DOC>